    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model is accepted for the VAD context of use. The validation dataset spans the full COU operating envelope, quantitative output comparison metrics satisfy pre-specified thresholds, and Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification has been performed across all primary input parameters. Minor discretization uncertainty in the hemolysis scalar transport and partial geometric dissimilarity between the validation benchmark and the target device are acknowledged as standard engineering caveats; these are judged not to materially affect the reliability of the hemolysis predictions given the conservative clinical acceptance margin applied. On balance, the evidence supports model acceptance for regulatory submission.",
